  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations in District of Columbia for FY2026 to date total $19.2B across 30,066 awards, with an average award size of $638K. Obligations are down 39.0% year over year. Annual obligations peaked at $35.9B in FY24 and have moved to $31.4B in FY25 and $19.2B in FY26 to date. The Department of Defense, Department of Transportation, and General Services Administration are the largest buying agencies in FY2026 to date with $3.6B, $2.6B, and $2.4B respectively. Top vendors include BOOZ ALLEN HAMILTON INC at $776M and HARRIS CORPORATION at $690M. Spending is concentrated in technology and professional services industries: Computer Systems Design Services is $2.8B and Engineering Services is $2.4B for FY2026 to date. Other sizable industry buckets are Other Computer Related Services at $2.1B and Administrative Management and General Management Consulting Services at $1.3B. These figures are fiscal year to date and represent contract obligations only.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How large is FY2026 federal contracting activity in DC compared with recent years?",
        "body": "Total obligations for FY2026 to date are $19.2B, down 39.0% year over year. By comparison, obligations were $31B in FY21, $31.6B in FY22, $33.9B in FY23, $35.9B in FY24, and $31.4B in FY25."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies, vendors, and industries drive spending in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The top buying agencies are Department of Defense ($3.6B), Department of Transportation ($2.6B), and General Services Administration ($2.4B). Leading vendors are BOOZ ALLEN HAMILTON INC ($776M), HARRIS CORPORATION ($690M), and SCIENCE APPLICATIONS INTERNATIONAL CORPORATION ($539M). Major industry totals include Computer Systems Design Services ($2.8B), Engineering Services ($2.4B), and Other Computer Related Services ($2.1B)."
      }
    ]
